    • calculateGENIE3importanceIteratively

      public HashMap<String,double[][]> calculateGENIE3importanceIteratively(ClusNode root, ClusStatManager statManager)
      An iterative version of calculateGENIE3importance(si.ijs.kt.clus.algo.tdidt.ClusNode,si.ijs.kt.clus.main.ClusRun), which does not update feature importances in place. Rather, it returns the partial importances for all attributes. These are combined later.

    • calculateSYMBOLICimportanceIteratively

      public HashMap<String,double[][]> calculateSYMBOLICimportanceIteratively(ClusNode root, String[] weights) throws InterruptedException
      Computes partial symbolic importances for all attributes. These are combined later into the final score. The partial importance of attribute is sum of the values

      0.0 : w^(depth of the node)? node has attribute as a test

      over the nodes in the tree, where parameter 0 < w <= 1. If w = SettingsEnsemble.DYNAMIC, then we add either 0 or weight of examples in node / weight of examples in root. The final score is the sum of partial importances.

      Parameters:
      root - Root of the tree
      weights - string representation of the weights, e.g., ["0.4", "DYNAMIC"].
      Returns:
      Partial importances
      Throws:
      InterruptedException

    • getInternalNodesWithDepth

      public ArrayList<NodeDepthPair> getInternalNodesWithDepth(ClusNode root)
      Finds all internal nodes in the given tree. Depth first search is used to traverse the tree. We return the nodes and their depths.
      Parameters:
      root - The root of the tree
      Returns:
      List of NodeDepthPair pairs
